### Instruction:
Write a web page that uses JavaScript to provide a button to turn your cat red. The button and the cat should be visible on the page.
### Response:
The code for the web page that turns your cat red is as follows:

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Turn Your Cat Red</title>
</head>
<body>
<img src="cat.jpg" alt="Cat">
<p>Click the button below to turn your cat red:</p>
<button onclick="toggleRedColor()">Turn Red</button>
<script>
function toggleRedColor() {
  var cat = document.getElementById('cat');
  if (cat.style.backgroundColor === 'red') {
    cat.style.backgroundColor = 'orange';
    document.querySelector('button').textContent = 'Turn Red';
  } else {
    cat.style.backgroundColor = 'red';
    document.querySelector('button').textContent = 'Turn Orange';
  }
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
```
